007package renderer.models_TP;
008
009import renderer.scene.*;
010import renderer.scene.primitives.*;
011import renderer.scene.util.MeshMaker_TP;
012import renderer.scene.util.MeshType;
013
014/**
015   Create a solid model of a partial right circular cylinder
016   with its axis along the y-axis.
017<p>
018   By a partial cylinder we mean a cylinder over a circular sector
019   of the cylinder's base.
020<p>
021   See <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Circular_sector" target="_top">
022                https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Circular_sector</a>
023
024   @see Cylinder
025   @see CircleSector
026   @see DiskSector
027   @see RingSector
028   @see ConeSector
029   @see SphereSector
030   @see TorusSector
031*/
032public class CylinderSector extends Model implements MeshMaker_TP
033{
034   public final double r;
035   public final double h;
036   public final double theta1;
037   public final double theta2;
038   public final int n;
039   public final int k;
040   public final MeshType type;
041
042   /**
043      Create half of a cylinder with radius 1
044      and its axis along the y-axis from
045      {@code y = 1} to {@code y = -1}.
046   */
047   public CylinderSector( )
048   {
049      this(1, 1, Math.PI/2, 3*Math.PI/2, 15, 8, MeshType.HORIZONTAL);
050   }
051
052
053   /**
054      Create a part of the cylinder with radius {@code r} and its
055      axis along the y-axis from {@code y = h} to {@code y = -h}.
056   <p>
057      The partial cylinder is a cylinder over the circular sector
058      from angle {@code theta1} to angle {@code theta2} (in the
059      counterclockwise direction).
060   <p>
061      The last two parameters determine the number of lines of longitude
062      and the number of (partial) circles of latitude in the model.
063   <p>
064      If there are {@code n} circles of latitude in the model, then
065      each line of longitude will have {@code n-1} line segments.
066      If there are {@code k} lines of longitude, then each (partial)
067      circle of latitude will have {@code k-1} line segments.
068   <p>
069      There must be at least four lines of longitude and at least
070      two circles of latitude.
071
072      @param r       radius of the cylinder
073      @param h       height of the cylinder (from h to -h along the y-axis)
074      @param theta1  beginning longitude angle of the sector (in radians)
075      @param theta2  ending longitude angle of the sector (in radians)
076      @param n       number of circles of latitude around the cylinder
077      @param k       number of lines of longitude
078      @throws IllegalArgumentException if {@code n} is less than 2
079      @throws IllegalArgumentException if {@code k} is less than 4
080   */
081   public CylinderSector(final double r, final double h,
082                         final double theta1, final double theta2,
083                         final int n, final int k)
084   {
085      this(r, h, theta1, theta2, n, k, MeshType.HORIZONTAL);
086   }
087
088
089   /**
090      Create a part of the cylinder with radius {@code r} and its
091      axis along the y-axis from {@code y = h} to {@code y = -h}.
092   <p>
093      The partial cylinder is a cylinder over the circular sector
094      from angle {@code theta1} to angle {@code theta2} (in the
095      counterclockwise direction).
096   <p>
097      The last two parameters determine the number of lines of longitude
098      and the number of (partial) circles of latitude in the model.
099   <p>
100      If there are {@code n} circles of latitude in the model, then
101      each line of longitude will have {@code n-1} line segments.
102      If there are {@code k} lines of longitude, then each (partial)
103      circle of latitude will have {@code k-1} line segments.
104   <p>
105      There must be at least four lines of longitude and at least
106      two circles of latitude.
107
108      @param r       radius of the cylinder
109      @param h       height of the cylinder (from h to -h along the y-axis)
110      @param theta1  beginning longitude angle of the sector (in radians)
111      @param theta2  ending longitude angle of the sector (in radians)
112      @param n       number of circles of latitude around the cylinder
113      @param k       number of lines of longitude
114      @param type    choose between horizoantal, vertical, and checkerboard triangle strips
115      @throws IllegalArgumentException if {@code n} is less than 2
116      @throws IllegalArgumentException if {@code k} is less than 4
117   */
118   public CylinderSector(final double r, final double h,
119                         double theta1, double theta2,
120                         final int n, final int k,
121                         final MeshType type)
122   {
123      super(String.format("Cylinder_Sector(%.2f,%.2f,%.2f,%.2f,%d,%d)",
124                                           r, h, theta1, theta2, n, k));
125
126      if (n < 2)
127         throw new IllegalArgumentException("n must be greater than 1");
128      if (k < 4)
129         throw new IllegalArgumentException("k must be greater than 3");
130
131      theta1 = theta1 % (2*Math.PI);
132      theta2 = theta2 % (2*Math.PI);
133      if (theta1 < 0) theta1 = 2*Math.PI + theta1;
134      if (theta2 < 0) theta2 = 2*Math.PI + theta2;
135      if (theta2 <= theta1) theta2 = theta2 + 2*Math.PI;
136
137      this.r = r;
138      this.h = h;
139      this.theta1 = theta1;
140      this.theta2 = theta2;
141      this.n = n;
142      this.k = k;
143      this.type = type;
144
145      // Create the cylinder's geometry.
146
147      final double deltaH = (2 * h) / (n - 1),
148                   deltaTheta = (theta2 - theta1)/ (k - 1);
149
150      // An array of vertices to be used to create triangles.
151      final Vertex[][] v = new Vertex[n][k];
152
153      // Create all the vertices.
154      for (int j = 0; j < k; ++j) // choose an angle of longitude
155      {
156         final double c = Math.cos(theta1 + j*deltaTheta),
157                      s = Math.sin(theta1 + j*deltaTheta);
158         for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) // choose a circle of latitude
159         {
160            v[i][j] = new Vertex( r * c,
161                                  h - i * deltaH,
162                                 -r * s );
163         }
164      }
165      final Vertex topCenter    = new Vertex(0,  h, 0),
166                   bottomCenter = new Vertex(0, -h, 0);
167
168      // Add all of the vertices to this model.
169      for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
170      {
171         for (int j = 0; j < k; ++j)
172         {
173            addVertex( v[i][j] );
174         }
175      }
176      addVertex(topCenter,
177                bottomCenter);
178      final int topCenterIndex    = n * k,
179                bottomCenterIndex = n * k + 1;
180
181      // Create all the triangle strips around the cylinder wall.
182      if (MeshType.HORIZONTAL == type)
183      {
184         for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; ++i) // choose a circle of latitude
185         {
186            final Primitive triStrip = new TriangleStrip();
187            for (int j = 0; j < k; ++j) // choose a line of longitude
188            {
189               triStrip.addIndex(   i * k + j); // v[i  ][j]
190               triStrip.addIndex((1+i)* k + j); // v[i+1][j]
191            }
192            addPrimitive(triStrip);
193         }
194      }
195      // Create all the triangle strips between the top and bottom.
196      else if (MeshType.VERTICAL == type)
197      {
198         for (int j = 0; j < k - 1; ++j) // choose a line of longitude
199         {
200            final Primitive triStrip = new TriangleStrip();
201            triStrip.addIndex(topCenterIndex);
202            for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) // choose a circle of latitude
203            {
204               triStrip.addIndex(i * k + j);    // v[i][j  ]
205               triStrip.addIndex(i * k + j+1);  // v[i][j+1]
206            }
207            triStrip.addIndex(bottomCenterIndex);
208            addPrimitive(triStrip);
209         }
210      }
211      else // MeshType.CHECKER triangle strips
212      {
213         for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; ++i) // choose a circle of latitude
214         {
215            for (int j = 0; j < k - 1; ++j) // choose a line of longitude
216            {
217               addPrimitive(
218                  new TriangleStrip(   i * k + j,       // v[i  ][j  ]
219                                    (1+i)* k + j,       // v[i+1][j  ]
220                                       i * k + j + 1,   // v[i  ][j+1]
221                                    (1+i)* k + j + 1)); // v[i+1][j+1]
222            }
223         }
224      }
225
226      // Create triangle fans at the top and bottom.
227      if ( MeshType.HORIZONTAL == type
228        || MeshType.CHECKER == type )
229      {
230         // Create the triangle fan at the top.
231         final Primitive topFan = new TriangleFan();
232         topFan.addIndex(topCenterIndex);
233         for (int j = 0; j < k; ++j)
234         {
235            topFan.addIndex( j );  // v[0][j]
236         }
237         addPrimitive(topFan);
238
239         // Create the triangle fan at the bottom.
240         final Primitive botFan = new TriangleFan();
241         botFan.addIndex(bottomCenterIndex);
242         for (int j = k - 1; j >= 0; --j)
243         {
244             botFan.addIndex( ((n-1)*k)+j );  // v[n-1][j]
245         }
246         addPrimitive(botFan);
247      }
248   }
249
250
251   // Implement the MeshMaker_TP interface (four methods).
252   @Override public int getHorzCount() {return n;}
253
254   @Override public int getVertCount() {return k;}
255
256   @Override public MeshType getType() {return type;}
257
258   @Override
259   public CylinderSector remake(final int n, final int k, final MeshType type)
260   {
261      return new CylinderSector(this.r, this.h,
262                                this.theta1, this.theta2,
263                                n, k,
264                                type);
265   }
266}//CylinderSector
